    {
      "content": "in rayleigh scattering the higher energy the light the stronger it scatters, and it just so happens that the light most bounced around, not direct sunlight that you see staring into the sun, is because it is the highest energy light that your eyes can see. ",
      "intimacy_delta": 0.01,
      "role": "Kurisu",
      "timestamp": "20:30",
      "timestampManuallyEdited": true
    },
    {
      "content": "Well, you can see violet too. Its just that its not as dominated by the solar spectrum and your eyes aren't as sensitive",
